        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Imagination is more important than keowledge.                                Einstein</ot>
          <tt>想象力比知识更重要。                                                      ----爱因斯坦</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>imagination</txt>
              <pro>[i,mædʒi'neiʃən]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n. 想象力；幻想物;空想</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>more ... than</txt>
              <def>多于；超出；比……多</def>
                <clon>
                  <c>more</c>
		  <c>than</c>
                </clon>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Activity is the only road to knowledge.                        Bernard Shaw</ot>
          <tt>行动是通往知识的唯一道路。                                         ---- 萧伯纳</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>activity</txt>
              <pro>[æk'tivəti]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n. 活动；活跃；行动</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>knowledge</txt>
              <pro>['nɔlidʒ]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n. 知识，学问；知道，认识；</def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Don't gild the lily.                                Shakespeare</ot>
          <tt>不要画蛇添足。                                    ---- 莎士比亚</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>gild</txt>
              <pro>[gild]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>vt. 镀金；虚饰；供给钱</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>lily</txt>
              <pro>['lili]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n. 百合花,百合;洁白之物; adj. 洁白的，纯洁的</def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>A novel is a mirror walking alone a main road.                    Stendhcl</ot>
          <tt>一部小说犹如一面行走在大街上的镜子。                              ---- 司汤达</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>novel</txt>
              <pro>['nɔvəl]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n.小说；adj.新奇的；异常的</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>mirror</txt>
              <pro>['mirə]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n. 镜子,真实的写照,榜样; vt. 反映；反射</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>walk alone</txt>
              <def>独行 ；守望孤单</def>
                <clon>
                  <c>walking alone</c>
                </clon>	      
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Art is long, and times fleeting.                             Longfellow</ot>
          <tt>艺术是永恒的，时间却是瞬息即逝的。                           ---- 朗费罗</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>fleet</txt>
              <pro>[fli:t]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>adj. 快速的，敏捷的；n. 舰队；小河；港湾；vi. 疾驰；飞逝；掠过；vt. 消磨</def>
                <clon>
                  <c>fleeting</c>
                </clon>
           </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
